00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 27=

4
00:01:38,387 --> 00:01:39,667
Why isn't she letting him go home?

5
00:01:44,628 --> 00:01:45,227
Mrs. Deng,

6
00:01:46,068 --> 00:01:47,387
I shouldn't have said that.

7
00:01:47,387 --> 00:01:48,108
Can you just pretend

8
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:48,867
I didn't say anything?

9
00:01:49,147 --> 00:01:50,307
Why?

10
00:01:50,708 --> 00:01:51,587
Where will he stay, then?

11
00:01:51,667 --> 00:01:52,507
At your place?

12
00:01:53,108 --> 00:01:54,108
I shouldn't have mentioned it.

13
00:01:54,147 --> 00:01:55,068
So I won't

14
00:01:55,068 --> 00:01:55,988
say another word.

15
00:01:57,468 --> 00:01:58,108
What do you mean?

16
00:01:58,147 --> 00:01:58,748
You can't just

17
00:01:58,748 --> 00:01:59,348
stop halfway.

18
00:01:59,348 --> 00:02:00,628
Please don't push me.

19
00:02:00,628 --> 00:02:01,387
Haiyang has already

20
00:02:01,387 --> 00:02:02,387
fallen out with me over this.

21
00:02:02,548 --> 00:02:03,108
He said

22
00:02:03,387 --> 00:02:05,027
I'm always revealing

23
00:02:05,108 --> 00:02:06,628
things about him to you,

24
00:02:07,068 --> 00:02:08,468
as though I'm trying to
make him look pitiful

25
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:09,828
in front of you.

26
00:02:11,748 --> 00:02:12,507
What's really going on?

27
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:13,267
Tell me.

28
00:02:13,428 --> 00:02:14,148
No.

29
00:02:14,227 --> 00:02:15,267
I've already said enough.

30
00:02:15,707 --> 00:02:17,107
I'm not saying another word,
no matter what.

31
00:02:17,348 --> 00:02:18,667
- Not a word?
- That's right.

32
00:02:19,827 --> 00:02:20,348
Alright.

33
00:02:21,547 --> 00:02:22,987
Mrs. Deng...

34
00:02:23,787 --> 00:02:24,707
Didn't his mother

35
00:02:24,947 --> 00:02:25,868
go to your workplace

36
00:02:25,908 --> 00:02:27,428
and put up a big poster?

37
00:02:28,588 --> 00:02:30,348
Haiyang got really upset
when he found out.

38
00:02:30,588 --> 00:02:31,387
After he went home,

39
00:02:31,428 --> 00:02:32,227
he had a huge fight with his mother.

40
00:02:32,308 --> 00:02:33,267
Then he packed up and left.

41
00:02:33,468 --> 00:02:35,267
He's been staying in my wife's warehouse
all this time.

42
00:02:39,588 --> 00:02:40,468
Living in the warehouse?

43
00:02:41,148 --> 00:02:42,028
Are you serious?

44
00:02:43,348 --> 00:02:45,148
I told Haiyang,

45
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,987
just spend a little money
and rent a place.

46
00:02:48,787 --> 00:02:50,748
He said he's saving up

47
00:02:51,148 --> 00:02:51,987
to pay you back.

48
00:02:52,468 --> 00:02:53,308
Renting a place

49
00:02:53,628 --> 00:02:54,748
is too wasteful.

50
00:04:06,028 --> 00:04:07,308
Why isn't it boiling?

51
00:04:07,507 --> 00:04:09,628
What kind of stove is this?

52
00:04:12,787 --> 00:04:13,748
What's going on?

53
00:04:16,387 --> 00:04:17,188
Deng Haiyang.

54
00:04:31,428 --> 00:04:32,788
Why are you here?

55
00:04:33,308 --> 00:04:33,748
I...

56
00:04:34,628 --> 00:04:35,188
No...

57
00:04:35,668 --> 00:04:36,347
You...

58
00:04:36,507 --> 00:04:36,907
Hang on.

59
00:04:37,108 --> 00:04:37,467
Hang on.

60
00:04:37,668 --> 00:04:38,027
Wait.

61
00:04:38,188 --> 00:04:38,548
Wait right there.

62
00:04:38,788 --> 00:04:39,347
Don't go anywhere.

63
00:04:41,068 --> 00:04:41,748
Just give me a second.

64
00:04:42,068 --> 00:04:42,748
Why didn't you tell me

65
00:04:43,108 --> 00:04:44,267
you were coming?

66
00:04:44,668 --> 00:04:45,228
I...

67
00:04:46,628 --> 00:04:47,947
I wasn't prepared at all.

68
00:04:47,947 --> 00:04:48,387
Look,

69
00:04:48,387 --> 00:04:49,188
it's so messy here.

70
00:04:50,188 --> 00:04:51,907
It's so hot today. Are you hot?

71
00:04:52,308 --> 00:04:53,907
No worries, I have a fan.

72
00:04:54,548 --> 00:04:55,467
I'll move it over for you.

73
00:04:58,147 --> 00:04:59,387
Alright, stop fussing around.

74
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:05,108
It's fine.

75
00:05:07,308 --> 00:05:07,907
It's fine.

76
00:05:08,628 --> 00:05:09,748
The cord's too short.

77
00:05:10,548 --> 00:05:11,707
Come, have a seat.

78
00:05:11,868 --> 00:05:12,507
Sit down for a bit.

79
00:05:13,027 --> 00:05:13,628
Take a rest.

80
00:05:14,027 --> 00:05:15,587
I'll get you a glass of water, alright?

81
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:17,827
Water...

82
00:05:19,707 --> 00:05:20,988
It's so hot here.

83
00:05:28,347 --> 00:05:29,108
Here.

84
00:05:29,108 --> 00:05:29,947
Thank you.

85
00:05:29,988 --> 00:05:30,827
Don't mention it.

86
00:05:37,947 --> 00:05:39,147
Why didn't you tell me?

87
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:41,147
Tell you what?

88
00:05:41,947 --> 00:05:42,748
That you had a fight with your mom

89
00:05:42,827 --> 00:05:43,788
and had nowhere to stay.

90
00:05:44,228 --> 00:05:45,228
Why didn't you let me know?

91
00:05:45,587 --> 00:05:46,108
It's...

92
00:05:47,027 --> 00:05:48,027
It's not a big deal,

93
00:05:48,068 --> 00:05:48,827
right?

94
00:05:54,748 --> 00:05:56,347
Don't torture yourself.

95
00:05:56,628 --> 00:05:57,587
Just rent a place.

96
00:05:59,308 --> 00:05:59,827
But...

97
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:00,988
Isn't this place fine?

98
00:06:01,147 --> 00:06:02,947
Look at this place.

99
00:06:03,907 --> 00:06:04,628
It's so spacious.

100
00:06:05,387 --> 00:06:06,108
Right? And besides,

101
00:06:06,387 --> 00:06:07,587
renting is too wasteful.

102
00:06:07,827 --> 00:06:09,027
I can live with this.

103
00:06:17,147 --> 00:06:18,228
About our savings,

104
00:06:18,387 --> 00:06:19,147
you don't have to pay me back.

105
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:20,188
Even if you do, I won't take it.

106
00:06:20,507 --> 00:06:21,188
No way.

107
00:06:22,587 --> 00:06:24,267
I said I'd pay it back,

108
00:06:25,827 --> 00:06:26,907
whether you like it or not.

109
00:06:46,308 --> 00:06:47,188
Here, I got you something to eat.

110
00:06:49,027 --> 00:06:49,587
Goodbye.

111
00:06:50,628 --> 00:06:51,188
Xiang Zhong.

112
00:06:51,189 --> 00:06:52,999
♪Something will eventually be lost♪

113
00:06:53,786 --> 00:06:55,786
♪Never to be remembered♪

114
00:06:55,788 --> 00:06:56,788
I'll practice

115
00:06:57,467 --> 00:06:59,467
driving with you later, okay?

116
00:07:00,928 --> 00:07:03,843
♪And then forgotten♪

117
00:07:04,403 --> 00:07:07,782
♪Who can still face life?♪

118
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,663
♪With the courage it gives♪

119
00:07:11,068 --> 00:07:12,027
It's fine.

120
00:07:13,587 --> 00:07:15,507
You just got out of the hospital,
take it easy.

121
00:07:15,509 --> 00:07:17,786
♪We must stay together♪

122
00:07:17,788 --> 00:07:19,228
I can drive pretty well now.

123
00:07:19,229 --> 00:07:22,147
♪Walking through the cool night breeze♪

124
00:07:22,148 --> 00:07:24,997
♪Leaving not a trace of sadness♪

125
00:07:25,957 --> 00:07:29,160
♪Those nights returning to moonlight♪

126
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:32,227
♪There will be someone thinking of you♪

127
00:07:33,034 --> 00:07:36,266
♪Treading a path of stars and seas♪

128
00:07:36,613 --> 00:07:39,287
♪Passing through the dawn♪

129
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:43,415
♪A familiar piece, a strange piece♪

130
00:07:43,815 --> 00:07:46,890
♪All are fleeting encounters♪

131
00:08:34,827 --> 00:08:36,108
You're home early today.

132
00:08:37,188 --> 00:08:38,428
I'm going to interview a new nanny.

133
00:08:39,987 --> 00:08:42,188
I'm just grabbing a few essentials today.

134
00:08:42,308 --> 00:08:43,587
Once I rent a place,

135
00:08:44,028 --> 00:08:45,388
I'll move the rest of the stuff out.

136
00:08:56,388 --> 00:08:57,227
Family Card.

137
00:08:58,148 --> 00:09:00,227
It's yours, you know the PIN.

138
00:10:11,707 --> 00:10:12,587
Ms. Xiang.

139
00:10:14,188 --> 00:10:15,068
Jiaqiao.

140
00:10:15,908 --> 00:10:16,947
You're back?

141
00:10:18,627 --> 00:10:20,388
I broke up with Lv Liang.

142
00:10:23,388 --> 00:10:24,068
What happened?

143
00:10:25,627 --> 00:10:26,268
We had

144
00:10:26,707 --> 00:10:27,908
set up the studio,

145
00:10:28,188 --> 00:10:29,188
registered the company,

146
00:10:29,548 --> 00:10:30,347
and even had talks
with investors.

147
00:10:30,587 --> 00:10:32,148
We were almost ready to sign contracts.

148
00:10:32,388 --> 00:10:33,188
But suddenly,

149
00:10:33,987 --> 00:10:35,188
all the investors backed out,

150
00:10:35,627 --> 00:10:36,467
and all the previous clients

151
00:10:36,587 --> 00:10:38,467
gave us the red light.

152
00:10:40,987 --> 00:10:42,148
There's nothing I can do now.

153
00:10:43,388 --> 00:10:45,347
I became a burden to him.

154
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:49,508
Xiang Nan,

155
00:10:50,908 --> 00:10:51,668
come down here for a second.

156
00:10:53,347 --> 00:10:55,068
He's been in a bad mood
ever since he came back.

157
00:11:06,347 --> 00:11:06,827
What's this?

158
00:11:07,148 --> 00:11:08,028
Look.

159
00:11:09,587 --> 00:11:10,548
Isn't this

160
00:11:10,668 --> 00:11:11,668
what you asked me to make?

161
00:11:12,587 --> 00:11:13,388
Do you know

162
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:14,508
what a three-legged toad is?

163
00:11:17,068 --> 00:11:17,788
What is this?

164
00:11:19,308 --> 00:11:20,068
This is just

165
00:11:20,068 --> 00:11:21,388
a normal toad.

166
00:11:22,548 --> 00:11:23,827
Are you messing with me?

167
00:11:24,508 --> 00:11:26,347
Look it up online.

168
00:11:26,707 --> 00:11:28,347
They're the same thing.

169
00:11:28,707 --> 00:11:29,867
Do you know how I felt today

170
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:30,827
at Biao's restaurant?

171
00:11:32,068 --> 00:11:33,467
Everyone was calling me an idiot

172
00:11:33,467 --> 00:11:34,867
behind my back.

173
00:11:36,308 --> 00:11:37,268
Are you happy

174
00:11:37,347 --> 00:11:38,388
that I looked like a fool?

175
00:11:41,148 --> 00:11:42,707
You call this a three-legged toad?

176
00:11:57,227 --> 00:11:58,227
Why do you have to

177
00:11:58,308 --> 00:12:00,747
always confront my brother head-on?

178
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,867
I've learned something recently.

179
00:12:05,268 --> 00:12:05,788
In the past,

180
00:12:06,068 --> 00:12:07,467
I would butt heads with him.

181
00:12:07,867 --> 00:12:08,707
Like an egg striking a stone,

182
00:12:08,908 --> 00:12:10,388
I ended up hurting myself.

183
00:12:11,107 --> 00:12:12,227
But what if I

184
00:12:12,707 --> 00:12:14,227
take a roundabout approach?

185
00:12:15,747 --> 00:12:16,548
For example,

186
00:12:18,987 --> 00:12:21,388
I've broken up with Lv Liang.

187
00:12:22,148 --> 00:12:23,587
Then all the funds and clients

188
00:12:23,747 --> 00:12:24,947
are back in play.

189
00:12:25,747 --> 00:12:26,827
Once he's doing well,

190
00:12:26,947 --> 00:12:28,467
we can get back together.

191
00:12:29,188 --> 00:12:30,947
Then no one can stop us.

192
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:34,867
But how do you know

193
00:12:35,347 --> 00:12:36,508
he'll wait for you?

194
00:12:37,068 --> 00:12:37,908
Because the two of us

195
00:12:38,028 --> 00:12:39,548
have always been together.

196
00:12:42,747 --> 00:12:44,308
We're going underground now.

197
00:12:44,827 --> 00:12:45,668
So from now on,

198
00:12:45,707 --> 00:12:46,987
you'll have to cover for me.

199
00:12:49,188 --> 00:12:50,308
Aren't you afraid I'll snitch?

200
00:12:52,148 --> 00:12:53,148
I know you won't.

201
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:54,627
Otherwise,

202
00:12:54,707 --> 00:12:55,508
you wouldn't have helped me

203
00:12:55,747 --> 00:12:56,627
hide it from my brother

204
00:12:56,747 --> 00:12:57,707
when we first got together.

205
00:12:58,428 --> 00:12:59,548
I regret it.

206
00:13:01,627 --> 00:13:02,707
When your brother finds out

207
00:13:02,788 --> 00:13:04,107
that we've both been hiding it from him,

208
00:13:04,308 --> 00:13:05,788
he's going to punish me again.

209
00:13:07,268 --> 00:13:08,668
That's why

210
00:13:09,627 --> 00:13:11,308
we need to use this kind of

211
00:13:11,308 --> 00:13:13,627
roundabout strategy.

212
00:13:14,467 --> 00:13:15,148
Right?

213
00:13:15,587 --> 00:13:16,987
Strategy.

214
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:19,587
You're using strategies now?

215
00:13:20,347 --> 00:13:21,347
I've become wiser now.

216
00:13:22,668 --> 00:13:23,668
I've grown up.

217
00:13:24,388 --> 00:13:25,508
But Jiaqiao,

218
00:13:28,668 --> 00:13:30,227
if family members

219
00:13:30,347 --> 00:13:32,268
have to play mind games like this,

220
00:13:32,987 --> 00:13:34,347
are they really family?

221
00:13:36,627 --> 00:13:37,947
Family...

222
00:13:40,747 --> 00:13:41,388
Xiang Nan,

223
00:13:42,068 --> 00:13:43,347
tell me honestly,

224
00:13:44,268 --> 00:13:46,188
are you happy with him?

225
00:14:02,987 --> 00:14:03,587
Let's eat.

226
00:14:10,908 --> 00:14:11,707
Ms. Xiang,

227
00:14:11,987 --> 00:14:12,867
all done.

228
00:14:13,788 --> 00:14:15,107
Thank you, Ms. Zhong.

229
00:14:15,947 --> 00:14:16,908
Can you come

230
00:14:16,987 --> 00:14:18,188
to work tomorrow?

231
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:19,587
Of course.

232
00:14:20,428 --> 00:14:21,428
Don't worry.

233
00:14:21,627 --> 00:14:22,668
I worked with my previous employer

234
00:14:22,668 --> 00:14:23,707
for over ten years.

235
00:14:24,028 --> 00:14:25,908
He told me that you were
college classmates.

236
00:14:26,347 --> 00:14:27,467
He even asked me

237
00:14:27,668 --> 00:14:29,388
to take good care

238
00:14:29,467 --> 00:14:30,428
of your two kids.

239
00:14:30,788 --> 00:14:31,308
I really

240
00:14:31,347 --> 00:14:32,627
enjoy working with kids.

241
00:14:32,908 --> 00:14:33,587
I'll be sure

242
00:14:33,788 --> 00:14:35,148
to do my best.

243
00:14:35,428 --> 00:14:36,388
That's great.

244
00:14:36,867 --> 00:14:38,947
For the first couple of days,

245
00:14:39,227 --> 00:14:40,268
someone will accompany you

246
00:14:40,308 --> 00:14:41,107
to pick up the kids.

247
00:14:41,388 --> 00:14:42,107
Either I

248
00:14:42,107 --> 00:14:43,587
or someone else from the family.

249
00:14:43,987 --> 00:14:44,587
Alright.

250
00:14:45,107 --> 00:14:46,308
Great, see you tomorrow.

251
00:14:46,508 --> 00:14:46,908
Alright.

252
00:14:47,068 --> 00:14:47,788
See you tomorrow.

253
00:14:47,908 --> 00:14:48,467
See you tomorrow.

254
00:14:48,508 --> 00:14:49,627
No need to see me out.

255
00:14:49,747 --> 00:14:50,947
You know the way out, right?

256
00:14:51,227 --> 00:14:51,788
Yes.

257
00:14:51,788 --> 00:14:52,347
I know the way.

258
00:14:52,508 --> 00:14:53,068
Alright, goodbye.

259
00:14:53,068 --> 00:14:53,467
Bye-bye.

260
00:14:53,548 --> 00:14:54,188
Bye-bye.

261
00:14:56,227 --> 00:14:57,548
Here, this is for you.

262
00:15:00,308 --> 00:15:01,148
And this too.

263
00:15:03,347 --> 00:15:04,148
(Chai Jin: Are you home?)

264
00:15:04,268 --> 00:15:05,467
(I'll come over in a bit.)

265
00:15:06,068 --> 00:15:06,627
(Xiang Qian: Yes, I'm here.)

266
00:15:14,668 --> 00:15:15,707
I've made up my mind.

267
00:15:15,788 --> 00:15:16,707
What do you two

268
00:15:17,548 --> 00:15:19,107
think of this caretaker?

269
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,987
She's alright.

270
00:15:21,788 --> 00:15:23,587
What about her cooking?

271
00:15:24,148 --> 00:15:25,028
Is it good?

272
00:15:26,107 --> 00:15:27,388
It's okay.

273
00:15:28,428 --> 00:15:29,347
What about you?

274
00:15:31,028 --> 00:15:32,268
It's alright.

275
00:15:34,428 --> 00:15:35,148
Alright.

276
00:15:35,148 --> 00:15:36,467
Mommy will tell her

277
00:15:36,788 --> 00:15:38,148
what foods you both like.

278
00:15:45,947 --> 00:15:46,627
Who's this?

279
00:15:47,908 --> 00:15:48,827
Keep sliding.

280
00:15:55,028 --> 00:15:55,788
What's this about?

281
00:15:57,028 --> 00:15:58,148
His name is Liu Wei.

282
00:15:58,548 --> 00:15:59,987
He's Li Shu's boyfriend.

283
00:16:01,068 --> 00:16:02,227
Actually, to be precise,

284
00:16:02,308 --> 00:16:03,068
it's Li Shu

285
00:16:03,227 --> 00:16:04,467
who intruded his family

286
00:16:04,747 --> 00:16:06,148
and became the mistress.

287
00:16:06,908 --> 00:16:07,627
So?

288
00:16:09,388 --> 00:16:10,268
So,

289
00:16:10,548 --> 00:16:11,268
Li Shu is pregnant

290
00:16:11,268 --> 00:16:12,548
with Liu Wei's child.

291
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:14,508
The one who gave me these photos

292
00:16:14,587 --> 00:16:15,707
is Liu Wei's wife.

